Instagram vs reality 🫠

I get alot of messages from some of you wanting to join yachting and I say DO IT⚓️

Yachting is fun, exciting, but don’t be fooled by cute instagram pictures and what you see on TV‼️

It’s extremely hard and the exhaustion is like no other 😪

I think I cleaned that shower at least 4 times in one day, extremely busy guests!!! I was SO DONE by the end of that charter 😪

Your girl was FULLY ready to be a stripper 😂

PS. Not working on this boat 
.
.
.
#yachtstewardess 
#belowdeck
#yachtlifestyle
#throwback

The hardest part about Yachting isn’t working on the yacht, it’s securing your first job ‼️ 

You think I work hard on a yacht, you have no idea how hard I worked to secure my first job!! It was no easy road for me in the beginning that’s for sure, but after readjusting my strategy I succeeded ⚓️ 

I get a lot of questions on How do I start? Where do I start? Any advice ? It’s confusing, overwhelming and some days I felt like just giving up the job search 🫠

SO I GET IT🤍 

I am hosting a Live Masterclass this Saturday 12pm EST and we will discuss EVERYTHING you need to know and the tips I learnt along the way ⚓️

Link in Bio ☝🏾

🔑 Does Popularity Translate to More Income?

Hey Sis! We get it. You see the massive potential of being a digital entrepreneur, but being the face of your brand? Not so much.

Do you really need online fame to make real-life money? Or is there a way to succeed without becoming "Insta-famous"? Join us this Wednesday on TWAA Live as we unravel this conundrum with:

🇿🇲 🇨🇦 @stellasata1, a financial advisor from Zambia (now based in Canada) who will spill the tea on whether or not online popularity results in sustainable wealth, or whether we’ll be brushing up our CVs at 60 cause we can’t afford to retire😮‍💨

🇰🇪 Our good Sis, Digital Entrepreneur and Thinkfluencer @just_ivy_africa will be joining us from Kenya to give us both perspectives - how much money she makes as a digital entrepreneur and celebrity in Kenya, and also as a money-savvy mom and founder of the 4000+ strong community of Money Movers

🇿🇦 🇺🇸 And finally, we’re SUPER excited to introduce to you Samke’ sister, @tumimhlongo joining us from New York. She’s a reality TV personality having appeared in Bravo’s Below Deck Down Under (go watch it, she’s hilarious) and she’ll tell us if reality TV pays as well as the stars make it seem, and what opportunities being on a popular American reality TV show has opened up for her. 

Hosted by @iamsamkemhlongo, let's debunk the fame-for-fortune myth! 🌟

Mark your calendar and don't miss it! ✨📆 #PopularityVsIncome #DigitalSuccess #RealityTVMoney

ITS FINALLY HERE!!!! 🤩

Whose ready for the wildest charter season EVER with the craziest crew🥲

My first time as Chief Stew⚓️
My first time chartering in the Med☀️What a WILD ride !!! 

#BelowDeckMed premieres September 25th on @BravoTV!

THANK YOU ALL SO SO MUCH for the overwhelming LOVE and support🥹 The messages, the texts, the phone calls 🤍

It can be very difficult working in an industry where their isn’t a lot of people like me and I would be lieing If I said I haven’t doubted myself a couple times!

But I always focused on working hard, growing, learning and removing myself from the politics and the BS!

Stay kind (don’t take shit though), stay humble, work hard and magic happens 👸🏾

CHEERS to a New Season🥂Get your popcorn ready, it’s going to be a WILD season🙊

I LOVE YOU ALL🤍🤍
